Here’s a *complete React example* demonstrating *CSS & Sass styling with data display*, including the folder setup, code, commands, and expected output.

---

## *React Program: CSS & Sass Styling*

### *1. Folder Setup*


my-app/
 ┣ src/
 ┃ ┣ App.js
 ┃ ┣ App.css
 ┃ ┣ App.scss
 ┃ ┗ index.js


---

### *2. Install Dependencies*

bash
# Create React project
npx create-vite my-react-app --template react
cd my-react-app

# Install dependencies
npm install
npm install sass


---

### **3. CSS File (App.css)**

css
.container {
  text-align: center;
  background-color: #f9f9f9;
  padding: 20px;
}

.title {
  color: #2c3e50;
  font-size: 2rem;
}


---

### **4. Sass File (App.scss)**

scss
$list-color: #27ae60;

.data-list {
  list-style: none;
  padding: 0;

  li {
    background: lighten($list-color, 30%);
    margin: 8px 0;
    padding: 10px;
    border-radius: 6px;
    font-weight: bold;

    &:hover {
      background: darken($list-color, 10%);
      color: #fff;
      cursor: pointer;
    }
  }
}


---

### **5. React Component (App.js)**

javascript
import React from "react";
import "./App.css";   // CSS
import "./App.scss";  // Sass

function App() {
  const fruits = ["Apple", "Banana", "Cherry", "Mango", "Orange"];

  return (
    <div className="container">
      <h1 className="title">Fruit List</h1>
      <ul className="data-list">
        {fruits.map((fruit, index) => (
          <li key={index}>{fruit}</li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </div>
  );
}

export default App;


---

### *6. Explanation*

1. App.js imports *CSS* and *Sass* for styling.
2. The fruits array is mapped to <li> elements.
3. App.css provides general styling like *container alignment* and *title color*.
4. App.scss demonstrates *Sass features*:

   * Variables ($list-color)
   * Nested styles
   * &:hover for hover effects
5. Hovering over a fruit item changes its background and text color.

---

### *7. Execution Steps*

bash
# Start development server
npm run dev


*Open in browser:* http://localhost:5173/

---

### *8. Output*


--------------------------------------
|                                    |
|          Fruit List                |
| [Apple]                            |
| [Banana]                           |
| [Cherry]                           |
| [Mango]                            |
| [Orange]                           |
|                                    |
--------------------------------------


* Each fruit has *light green background*.
* Hovering changes *background to dark green* and text to *white*.

---

This demonstrates *how to use both CSS and Sass in a React app* to style a list dynamically.

